text: Muslihan Diding Sutrisno (4 August 1946 - 6 December 2020) was an Indonesian military official and politician. He was born in Bengkulu, Indonesia. He was a member of the People's Conscience Party. DS was Regent of Rejang Lebong from 1994 to 1999 and of North Bengkulu from 2001 to 2006. DS died on 6 December 2020 in Bengkulu of COVID-19 at the age of 74.Cawagub Bengkulu Muslihan DS Meninggal karena Covid-19 ==References== Category:1946 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in Indonesia Category:Indonesian politicians Category:Bengkulu
